videos.headline: Darshan Nalkande to Ashutosh Sharma, out Caught by Rashid Khan!! Another twist in the tale! Darshan Nalkande doesn't have any emotions on his face! A superb cameo from Ashutosh Sharma though. Made a real impact! A slower back of a length ball on off, Ashutosh Sharma mistimes his flat-batted stroke towards long-on. Rashid doesn't have to move an inch and is safe as houses. Ashutosh Sharma c Rashid Khan b Darshan Nalkande 31(17) [4s-3 6s-1]

Rashid Khan to Jitesh Sharma, out Caught by Darshan Nalkande!! Can you believe it? He nailed the previous two balls but has mistimed the full-toss. Was right in the zone to be hit out of the ground but Jitesh Sharma mistimes his expansive shot towards deep mid-wicket. The fielder in the deep makes no mistake. Deep Dasgupta on air mentions that Rashid becomes the first GT bowler to take 50 wickets. Jitesh Sharma c Darshan Nalkande b Rashid Khan 16(8) [6s-2]

Mohit Sharma to Raza, out Caught by Saha!! Raza departs against the run of play! Mohit Sharma closes his eyes and thanks his stars! A back of a length ball outside off at 130 clicks, Raza tries to slap it through covers but the extra bounce induces the outside edge. Saha has to leap and takes it reverse cup near head height. Raza c Saha b Mohit Sharma 15(16)

Azmatullah to Sam Curran, out Caught by Williamson!! Soft dismissal! Azmatullah is over the moon and has a beaming smile on his face! A shortish delivery on off, Sam Curran pulls it with good timing but doesn't bother to keep it down. Hasn't found the gap as it flies straight towards Williamson at mid-wicket and he doesn't drop those. PBKS are in deep trouble now. Sam Curran c Williamson b Azmatullah 5(8)

Noor Ahmad to Prabhsimran, out Caught by Mohit Sharma!! It's Noor Ahmad once again who delivers with the googly! Brilliant bowlng from the chinaman. He spots Prabhsimran backing away and bowls a googly on a fuller length on off. Prabhsimran looks to go over covers as it turns away from him and only manages to edge it towards backward point. Mohit Sharma accepts it gleefully. Prabhsimran c Mohit Sharma b Noor Ahmad 35(24) [4s-5 6s-1]

Noor Ahmad to Bairstow, out Bowled!! Bowled through the gate! Jonny Bairstow with a let me get a sighter kind of forward defence. There was just a very tiny bat pad gap. But Noor Ahmad did him in the air. Googly that sucked the batter into a forward defence, sneaked through the gate, brushed the pad and hit the off stump. This is a big wicket because Jonny was keen for a big hit. Bairstow b Noor Ahmad 22(13) [4s-4]

Umesh Yadav to Dhawan, out Bowled!! Oh chopped on! Umesh knows he's got lucky here. This was back of a length and outside off stump, Dhawan looks to cut with no much feet movement, probably came on slower and he dragged it back onto middle and leg stumps. Umesh looks up and smiles. GT will feel a lot better now with that wicket after the first over! Dhawan b Umesh Yadav 1(2)

Rabada to Shankar, out Caught by Harpreet Brar!! Short and slow into the wicket, Shankar tries to flat-bat this over the boundary like his partner but he's mishit this. Brar had to run in from long-off and he timed his forward dive to perfection! GT may not mind this wicket because it gets the hitters in now! Shankar c Harpreet Brar b Rabada 8(10)

Harshal Patel to Sai Sudharsan, out Caught by Jitesh Sharma!! Appeal for caught behind but Sai Sudharsan walks without waiting for the finger and the ump tells the bowler he's already walked. Smart ball by Harshal Patel. Slower delivery short and angling across, Sai Sudharsan tried to guide it to third man but had to adjust the bat swing because of lack of pace, seems to have gone off the bottom of the bat to the keeper (under edge actually). Lovely little cameo from Sai though. Came out with great intent and injected life into the innings after GT slipped a bit after the powerplay. Sai Sudharsan c Jitesh Sharma b Harshal Patel 33(19) [4s-6]

Harpreet Brar to Williamson, out Caught by Bairstow!! Brar strikes! Much needed for Punjab and it comes right after the break. Williamson would be disappointed because this was not a wicket-taking delivery. Short and outside off, Williamson cuts it straight to backward point and Bairstow didn't move an inch. He reverse cups it safely. It was the extra bounce that did not allow Williamson to keep the cut down. Williamson c Bairstow b Harpreet Brar 26(22) [4s-4]

Rabada to Saha, out Caught by Dhawan!! Rabada draws first blood. 143.9ks angled in and the ball lands around good length, Saha thinks he can flick it over the leg-side field and closes the bat face, he's a tad early and the leading edge goes straight up, Dhawan settles under it near extra cover. He takes the catch and does the thigh-five. This is the fourth time Rabada has got rid of Saha. Saha c Dhawan b Rabada 11(13) [4s-2]
